results.name: Decimal expansion of (1/105)*Pi^3.
comment: Conjectured to be density of densest packing of equal spheres in 7 dimensions (achieved for example by the E_7 lattice).
reference: J. H. Conway and N. J. A. Sloane, What are all the best sphere packings in low dimensions?, Discr. Comp. Geom., 13 (1995), 383-403.
J. H. Conway and N. J. A. Sloane, "Sphere Packings, Lattices and Groups", Springer, 3rd. ed., 1998. See p. xix.
link: G. Nebe and N. J. A. Sloane, Home page for E_7 lattice
N. J. A. Sloane, Table of maximal density of a packing of equal spheres in n-dimensional Euclidean space (for n>3 the values are only conjectural).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Feb 10 2013
